Copyright (c) 2026 HalkPapa

## 1. Definitions

"Software" refers to the LocalDBKit source code, documentation, and associated files.
"You" refers to the individual or entity exercising permissions under this License.
"Personal Use" means use for individual, non-commercial purposes.
"Commercial Use" means any use primarily intended for commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

## 2. Grant of Rights

Subject to the terms and conditions of this License, the copyright holder hereby grants You a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license to:

a) **Use** the Software for Personal Use purposes
b) **Copy** the Software for Personal Use purposes
c) **Modify** the Software for your own Personal Use (internal modifications only)
d) **Study** the Software for learning and educational purposes

## 3. Restrictions

You may NOT:

a) **Commercial Use**: Use the Software, in whole or in part, for any Commercial Use without explicit written permission from the copyright holder.

b) **Distribution of Modifications**: Distribute, publish, or share any modified versions of the Software, whether publicly or privately, even if modified for Personal Use.

c) **Sublicensing**: Grant sublicenses to the Software or any portion thereof.

d) **Redistribution**: Redistribute the original Software except by directing others to the official repository (https://github.com/HalkPapa/LocalDBKit).

## 4. Permitted Activities

You MAY:

a) **Fork** the repository on GitHub for your own Personal Use (private modifications)
b) **Share** the link to the official repository
c) **Contribute** to the official repository via pull requests (contributions become part of the original Software)
d) **Report** issues and bugs
e) **Make donations** to support the project (see FUNDING.yml)

## 5. Attribution

If you publicly reference, discuss, or create educational content about the Software, you must provide proper attribution to the original author (HalkPapa) and link to the official repository.

## 6. Commercial Use Inquiries

If you wish to use LocalDBKit for Commercial Use, please contact the copyright holder for licensing options.

Contact: https://github.com/HalkPapa

## 7. Contributions

By submitting a contribution (pull request, issue, suggestion) to the Software, you agree that:

a) Your contribution may be included in the Software under this License
b) You grant the copyright holder a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free license to use, modify, and distribute your contribution
c) You have the right to submit the contribution

## 8. Disclaimer of Warranty

THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT.

## 9. Limitation of Liability

IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.

## 10. Termination

This License automatically terminates if you violate any of its terms. Upon termination, you must cease all use of the Software and destroy all copies in your possession.

## 11. Governing Law

This License shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of Japan.

